cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.CR 

The paper addresses the problem of person re-identification, which is a computer vision task related to image and video analysis. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper proposes a novel approach based on a recurrent neural network (LSTM), which is a popular technique in machine learning and deep learning. Therefore, it is also likely to belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with human tracking and feature representation, which are topics related to multimedia analysis and retrieval, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper proposes a method for improving the discriminative power of feature representations, which is a topic related to security and privacy, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
